Jorge Cardenas, manager of Colombia'sCoffee Growers' Federation, welcomed Brazil's export measuresand said they clarified the market situation.    He told journalists the measures "set the rules clearly" andhelped dissipate whatever doubts the market might have hadabout the world's biggest exporter's policies.    Brazil's coffee institute, IBC, today opened exportregistrations for May with no quantity limit set. Thecontribution quota will be 15 pct of the minimum registrationprice, which will vary daily. Reuter&#3;